Grammy award winner Burna Boy has become the first Nigerian artiste to sell out all tickets at Accor Arena – a 20,300 capacity event centre in Paris, France. He also becomes the first Nigerian to sell out the venue twice in his career. The dancehall artiste delivered an energetic performance, playing some of his hit songs including “Ye” to the delight of music lovers at the SpaceDrift concert.   Nancy Isime denies alleged romance with UK businessman     Russian strike kills another Ukrainian film star     Flamboyant social media lifestyle doesn’t translate to…   Others who have performed on the big stage are creative pop stars, including Jay Z, Beyonce, Bruno Mars, Rihanna, Drake, and others. This makes it the fourth concert the popular music act has performed this year. He had recently performed to sold-out crowds in Dublin, Geneva, and Manchester respectively.